Question: in
Answer: + abl., in, + acc., into, toward, against
Name: in

Question: ad
Answer: + acc., to, up to, near to
Name: ad

Question: dē
Answer: + abl., down from, from; concerning, about
Name: dē

Question: ē, ex
Answer: + abl., out of, from within, from; by reason of, on account of; of (following cardinal numbers
Name: ē, ex

Question: sub
Answer: + abl., (w/ verbs of rest), + acc. (w/ verbs of motion), under, up under, close to; down to/into, to/at the foot of
Name: sub

Question: prō
Answer: + abl., in front of, before, on behalf of, in return for, instead of, for ,as
Name: prō

Question: propter
Answer: + acc., on account of, because of
Name: propter

Question: apud
Answer: + acc., among, in the presence of, at the house of
Name: apud
